info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 17 at 1:12PM MST until February 18 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 AM MST FRIDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected. Areas of blowing snow from recent snowfall. * WHERE...South Laramie Range and South Laramie Range Foothills. * WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 5 AM MST Friday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight and high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers, with a risk for blow overs. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Areas of blowing snow expected through tonight. Visibility will be reduced to one half mile at times.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
